1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,320 --> 00:01:37,682
=Episode 13=
(The Day We Couldn't Go Back To)

3
00:01:43,677 --> 00:01:44,518
Ren Meiyan.

4
00:01:49,677 --> 00:01:50,477
Open the door.

5
00:01:52,358 --> 00:01:53,078
Open the door.

6
00:01:55,317 --> 00:01:56,237
Open the door.

7
00:01:56,317 --> 00:01:58,477
Xiaoming, what's wrong?

8
00:01:59,278 --> 00:01:59,957
You have a try.

9
00:02:00,518 --> 00:02:01,998
Mom, open the door.

10
00:02:02,837 --> 00:02:03,918
- Let me try.
- Mom.

11
00:02:04,397 --> 00:02:05,518
Why did you lock the door?

12
00:02:05,597 --> 00:02:07,638
Meiyan.

13
00:02:08,118 --> 00:02:09,197
- Mom.
- Meiyan.

14
00:02:13,077 --> 00:02:13,678
What happened?

15
00:02:14,917 --> 00:02:15,558
- Mom.
- Meiyan.

16
00:02:16,158 --> 00:02:16,797
- Mom.
- Mom.

17
00:02:17,197 --> 00:02:17,838
- Mom.
- Mom.

18
00:02:18,037 --> 00:02:18,678
Careful.

19
00:02:18,838 --> 00:02:19,477
Mom.

20
00:02:23,672 --> 00:02:24,317
- After you.
- After you.

21
00:02:24,438 --> 00:02:25,432
Thanks.

22
00:02:26,678 --> 00:02:27,960
- Welcome.
- Sir.

23
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:29,037
- Find yourselves a seat.
- Okay.

24
00:02:29,637 --> 00:02:30,648
What'd you like to eat?

25
00:02:30,648 --> 00:02:32,536
The food here
is both cheap and delicious.

26
00:02:32,958 --> 00:02:35,158
You pick a good place, ma'am.

27
00:02:35,958 --> 00:02:38,118
I'll have the tomato and egg noodles.

28
00:02:38,558 --> 00:02:39,958
Is that all?

29
00:02:41,077 --> 00:02:42,718
- Make that two noodles.
- Got it!

30
00:02:42,878 --> 00:02:45,597
I'm saving you money, ma'am.

31
00:02:46,158 --> 00:02:47,077
- Good.
- Two sodas.

32
00:02:47,278 --> 00:02:47,917
- Okay.
- How much?

33
00:02:47,958 --> 00:02:49,757
- 30 in total.
- Okay, it's paid.

34
00:02:49,816 --> 00:02:50,597
Hold on, ma'am.

35
00:02:51,238 --> 00:02:52,158
Take the seat of honor.

36
00:02:52,678 --> 00:02:54,158
Why can't I sit here?

37
00:02:54,317 --> 00:02:55,757
- Seat of honor.
- Did your first love sit there?

38
00:02:55,917 --> 00:02:57,317
It's not like that.

39
00:02:57,398 --> 00:02:58,838
I always sit here every time I come.

40
00:02:59,438 --> 00:03:00,718
Look here, ma'am.

41
00:03:00,838 --> 00:03:03,037
Friendship Forever.

42
00:03:03,757 --> 00:03:05,158
Though I don't know who did this,

43
00:03:05,398 --> 00:03:07,197
there must be a story behind it.

44
00:03:09,317 --> 00:03:10,477
Your noodles, please.

45
00:03:10,597 --> 00:03:11,797
- Enjoy your meal.
- Thanks.

46
00:03:11,797 --> 00:03:12,696
Okay, thanks.

47
00:03:18,197 --> 00:03:19,077
- Thanks.
- You enjoy.

48
00:03:20,637 --> 00:03:22,238
What exactly did Ren Meiyan say?

49
00:03:24,838 --> 00:03:26,797
Good for you.

50
00:03:27,438 --> 00:03:29,158
You're doing quite well as an intern,

51
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:34,232
talking to me like my boss now, huh?

52
00:03:36,637 --> 00:03:38,398
Are you trying to take power?

53
00:03:38,398 --> 00:03:40,998
No, even if I wanted to do that,
with you ahead of me,

54
00:03:40,998 --> 00:03:42,238
I wouldn't get any chance.

55
00:03:44,118 --> 00:03:45,517
For those born after 2000 like you,

56
00:03:45,718 --> 00:03:47,238
- sometimes...
- Hold on.

57
00:03:47,718 --> 00:03:49,317
That isn't the point.

58
00:03:49,797 --> 00:03:52,517
Every era has its share
of upright idealists.

59
00:03:53,838 --> 00:03:56,958
For example, there's someone
born in the 1980s I admire.

60
00:03:58,278 --> 00:03:59,917
Her story made me apply

61
00:03:59,917 --> 00:04:02,718
to come to Qidaohezi after graduation.

62
00:04:03,197 --> 00:04:06,477
When she was a police intern,

63
00:04:06,917 --> 00:04:09,438
she always argued with the leadership.

64
00:04:09,917 --> 00:04:12,757
Back in 2012,
there was a poisoning case.

65
00:04:13,077 --> 00:04:16,558
The criminal made the victims
drink pesticide themselves.

66
00:04:17,077 --> 00:04:19,197
All the evidence pointed to suicide.

67
00:04:19,837 --> 00:04:21,918
Only that police intern,

68
00:04:22,157 --> 00:04:24,277
relying on sheer tenacity,

69
00:04:24,598 --> 00:04:26,798
managed to find a partial fingerprint.

70
00:04:27,238 --> 00:04:28,918
That turned the whole case around.

71
00:04:30,598 --> 00:04:33,438
That's why I admire her and revere her.

72
00:04:34,038 --> 00:04:35,397
- I respect her.
- Stop.

73
00:04:36,197 --> 00:04:38,077
Today, you win.

74
00:04:38,317 --> 00:04:39,038
You're the boss.

75
00:04:39,837 --> 00:04:40,757
I'll report to you.

76
00:04:40,757 --> 00:04:41,678
I'm listening.

77
00:04:44,678 --> 00:04:47,837
Ren Meiyan said that on the first day
of the Chinese New Year in 2007,

78
00:04:48,478 --> 00:04:50,238
she received a call from Wen Yuxiu.

79
00:04:50,717 --> 00:04:51,717
2007?

80
00:04:53,358 --> 00:04:54,238
That can't be right.

81
00:04:54,837 --> 00:04:57,277
Didn't Wen Yuxiu die in 2007?

82
00:04:59,798 --> 00:05:01,118
But Ren Meiyan said

83
00:05:01,397 --> 00:05:03,118
that she heard

84
00:05:04,038 --> 00:05:05,077
Wen Yuxiu's breathing.

85
00:05:06,238 --> 00:05:07,197
Breathing?

86
00:05:07,558 --> 00:05:09,397
Can it alone prove
it was from Wen Yuxiu?

87
00:05:09,478 --> 00:05:10,238
I heard it too.

88
00:05:10,238 --> 00:05:10,957
Nonsense!

89
00:05:13,998 --> 00:05:17,118
That's why I think I need to go
to Tubao Village, Shabei County,

90
00:05:17,517 --> 00:05:18,757
to find out the truth

91
00:05:19,438 --> 00:05:20,238
firsthand.

92
00:05:35,397 --> 00:05:35,998
You're awake.

93
00:05:38,238 --> 00:05:40,317
Xiaoming and Xiaofei just went out.

94
00:05:40,837 --> 00:05:41,678
Are you okay?

95
00:05:42,118 --> 00:05:43,478
High blood pressure. Can't be mad,

96
00:05:43,678 --> 00:05:44,918
or it raises blood pressure.

97
00:05:45,998 --> 00:05:46,598
Very high.

98
00:05:47,197 --> 00:05:49,157
I know about my illness.

99
00:05:50,558 --> 00:05:53,397
It's been five years.
I thought I was fine.

100
00:05:53,837 --> 00:05:56,238
I got into a relationship
and married you.

101
00:05:57,558 --> 00:05:59,637
But here it comes in the end.

102
00:06:00,918 --> 00:06:04,957
I shouldn't have married you.
I'm sorry to be such a burden.

103
00:06:05,798 --> 00:06:07,157
Come on.

104
00:06:08,277 --> 00:06:09,317
You're never a burden.

105
00:06:10,478 --> 00:06:14,038
If anyone dares say so,

106
00:06:14,957 --> 00:06:17,837
your soldier will go after them.

107
00:06:19,277 --> 00:06:21,118
Don't forget

108
00:06:22,678 --> 00:06:25,038
you're my dear princess.

109
00:06:30,157 --> 00:06:31,918
It's my fault.

110
00:06:32,717 --> 00:06:34,157
I'm your wife,

111
00:06:35,438 --> 00:06:37,438
but I can't grow old with you.

112
00:06:37,998 --> 00:06:39,957
I can grow old with you.

113
00:06:40,918 --> 00:06:43,118
You always say you're not a good mom,

114
00:06:43,757 --> 00:06:45,118
but I think you are

115
00:06:48,798 --> 00:06:50,798
the greatest mother.

116
00:06:51,878 --> 00:06:53,598
Don't tell the kids.

117
00:06:55,118 --> 00:06:56,438
It's not the right time yet.

118
00:06:58,558 --> 00:06:59,157
I won't.

119
00:07:02,757 --> 00:07:03,397
I won't.

120
00:07:04,317 --> 00:07:05,678
I'm here with you. Don't worry.

121
00:07:07,238 --> 00:07:08,478
Just focus on your recovery.

122
00:07:13,397 --> 00:07:15,077
Why did Mom lock her bedroom door?

123
00:07:20,438 --> 00:07:22,558
Did you fight about me again?

124
00:07:23,798 --> 00:07:24,397
No.

125
00:07:26,717 --> 00:07:27,918
Don't lie to me.

126
00:07:29,317 --> 00:07:32,077
I heard Mom and Uncle Li
whispering late at night.

127
00:07:32,717 --> 00:07:34,277
Mom always says she's worried about me,

128
00:07:35,238 --> 00:07:36,478
afraid nobody will care for me.

129
00:07:37,397 --> 00:07:39,438
She wants to send me
to Qingzhou to live with you.

130
00:07:41,277 --> 00:07:42,798
Did Mom mention this to you?

131
00:07:43,678 --> 00:07:44,517
No.

132
00:07:47,197 --> 00:07:49,157
Stop fighting over me.

133
00:07:51,157 --> 00:07:53,197
Just pretend to agree
with whatever Mom says.

134
00:07:54,317 --> 00:07:55,238
Don't worry about me.

135
00:07:55,837 --> 00:07:58,238
Even if Mom's gone someday,
you don't have to worry about me.

136
00:07:59,277 --> 00:08:00,757
I can manage to live.

137
00:08:01,197 --> 00:08:02,517
If I can't, I'll go join Mom.

138
00:08:05,077 --> 00:08:06,317
I don't want to be your burden.

139
00:08:08,438 --> 00:08:09,998
I've been a burden my whole life.

140
00:08:10,517 --> 00:08:12,238
This has nothing to do with you.

141
00:08:16,397 --> 00:08:18,517
I promise not to argue
with Mom anymore, okay?

142
00:08:20,038 --> 00:08:21,157
I'll be good too.

143
00:08:22,998 --> 00:08:24,438
We can't upset Mom anymore.

144
00:08:24,998 --> 00:08:26,238
We only have one mom.

145
00:08:27,077 --> 00:08:29,118
If we make her sick, we'll lose her.

146
00:08:37,318 --> 00:08:38,397
Mom will be okay.

147
00:08:41,277 --> 00:08:41,958
She will be fine.

148
00:08:46,998 --> 00:08:47,960
Xiaoming.

149
00:08:48,198 --> 00:08:49,037
- Uncle Li.
- Uncle Li.

150
00:08:50,517 --> 00:08:51,397
Don't worry.

151
00:08:51,677 --> 00:08:54,238
Your mom just has high blood pressure.

152
00:08:54,917 --> 00:08:55,998
It's under control now.

153
00:08:56,917 --> 00:08:57,557
Don't worry.

154
00:08:58,318 --> 00:08:59,557
Just don't upset her

155
00:09:01,517 --> 00:09:02,917
anymore, okay?

156
00:09:04,277 --> 00:09:06,718
It's late. You take Xiaofei home.

157
00:09:07,797 --> 00:09:08,958
I'll stay with your mom.

158
00:09:11,238 --> 00:09:11,917
Thank you.

159
00:09:12,998 --> 00:09:14,557
Not at all. We're family.

160
00:09:16,078 --> 00:09:17,318
Come on, let's go home.

161
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:19,878
Thanks, Uncle Li.

162
00:09:45,517 --> 00:09:46,157
Go to sleep.

163
00:09:46,677 --> 00:09:47,478
Good night.

164
00:09:51,157 --> 00:09:53,598
Xiaoming, I need to ask you something.

165
00:09:55,397 --> 00:09:56,037
What is it?

166
00:09:57,998 --> 00:10:00,037
You knew
that diary couldn't be revealed.

167
00:10:00,838 --> 00:10:03,238
Why sue him over it?

168
00:10:03,677 --> 00:10:05,797
Ren Xiaofei,
this has nothing to do with you.

169
00:10:06,797 --> 00:10:08,198
I'm not a kid anymore.

170
00:10:09,157 --> 00:10:10,157
My mind is clear.

171
00:10:10,397 --> 00:10:11,637
I haven't taken meds recently.

172
00:10:14,157 --> 00:10:15,277
Tell me the truth.

173
00:10:16,118 --> 00:10:17,198
What are you planning?

174
00:10:18,397 --> 00:10:19,198
Nothing.

175
00:10:24,238 --> 00:10:26,397
Is it you or Bai Shu?

176
00:10:34,677 --> 00:10:35,958
I can confess.

177
00:10:42,958 --> 00:10:43,878
Confess what?

178
00:10:44,797 --> 00:10:45,718
I'm willing to confess.

179
00:10:46,198 --> 00:10:47,397
I've burdened you all so long.

180
00:10:47,958 --> 00:10:49,677
- Going to jail is okay for me.
- Shut up!

181
00:10:50,238 --> 00:10:51,397
- I can confess.
- Go to sleep!

182
00:10:51,917 --> 00:10:53,517
Xiaoming, I want to confess.

183
00:10:57,277 --> 00:10:59,917
You've drifted farther from home.

184
00:11:00,598 --> 00:11:02,037
I know why you don't come back.

185
00:11:02,838 --> 00:11:04,478
Mom always made you care for me.

186
00:11:05,838 --> 00:11:07,157
And I always fought with you.

187
00:11:08,277 --> 00:11:09,838
You've bottled up resentment.

188
00:11:09,838 --> 00:11:10,557
I'm not resentful.

189
00:11:14,797 --> 00:11:16,078
Back in elementary school,

190
00:11:16,478 --> 00:11:17,958
you took me to the bathroom,

191
00:11:19,557 --> 00:11:22,677
but I was scared to be inside alone.

192
00:11:23,277 --> 00:11:24,757
I ran out and wet myself.

193
00:11:26,397 --> 00:11:27,397
Everyone laughed.

194
00:11:28,917 --> 00:11:29,757
Then I got sick.

195
00:11:32,557 --> 00:11:34,037
Mom blamed you for it.

196
00:11:34,917 --> 00:11:36,397
How could you not feel resentful?

197
00:11:40,437 --> 00:11:41,238
Ren Xiaofei.

198
00:11:44,198 --> 00:11:45,557
If you truly feel sorry for me,

199
00:11:46,517 --> 00:11:49,557
take care of Mom and yourself.

200
00:11:52,397 --> 00:11:54,757
Stop any wild idea. Got it?

201
00:11:56,397 --> 00:11:57,797
Xiaoming, I want to confess.

202
00:11:57,797 --> 00:12:00,078
Enough, go to bed. Come on.

203
00:12:01,277 --> 00:12:01,998
Be good.

204
00:12:12,478 --> 00:12:15,637
Lately, I often think of Bai Shu.

205
00:12:17,718 --> 00:12:21,157
I remember the day
when you celebrated my birthday.

206
00:12:23,917 --> 00:12:24,998
I was so happy.

207
00:12:27,557 --> 00:12:31,238
(Your happiness started
with my worn-out sneakers).

208
00:12:33,998 --> 00:12:35,797
These are this year's trendiest shoes.

209
00:12:36,037 --> 00:12:36,718
(Qidaohezi, 2006)
Take them.

210
00:12:38,998 --> 00:12:40,198
No, thanks.

211
00:12:42,157 --> 00:12:43,637
They only cost 8 yuan wholesale.

212
00:12:43,637 --> 00:12:45,677
Take them. It's okay.

213
00:12:46,958 --> 00:12:47,478
I can't.

214
00:12:47,838 --> 00:12:50,917
Your shoes are already worn-out.
Get new ones.

215
00:12:50,917 --> 00:12:51,998
Come on. Take them.

216
00:12:52,318 --> 00:12:53,838
I can provide you with shoes for life.

217
00:12:56,198 --> 00:12:58,437
I won't wear only 8-yuan shoes
my whole life.

218
00:12:59,718 --> 00:13:01,437
Give them back if you don't want them.

219
00:13:01,437 --> 00:13:02,637
They're already mine.

220
00:13:04,397 --> 00:13:06,078
But I can't accept your gift
for nothing.

221
00:13:13,598 --> 00:13:14,157
It's for you.

222
00:13:15,157 --> 00:13:18,437
This is a problem set compiled
by master teachers from our school.

223
00:13:18,797 --> 00:13:20,637
Many students try to get it.

224
00:13:21,078 --> 00:13:21,797
Okay, thanks.

225
00:13:23,437 --> 00:13:25,397
Don't forget to do it.

226
00:13:25,397 --> 00:13:26,397
I'll definitely do it.

227
00:13:26,598 --> 00:13:28,078
Tell me if you have any questions.

228
00:13:28,517 --> 00:13:29,078
Okay.

229
00:13:45,397 --> 00:13:46,118
Does it fit?

230
00:13:46,557 --> 00:13:47,598
It fits pretty well.

231
00:13:50,917 --> 00:13:52,437
How did you know my shoe size?

232
00:13:53,037 --> 00:13:54,437
I've read Sherlock Holmes.

233
00:13:54,437 --> 00:13:56,198
On a rainy day,
I measured your footprint.

234
00:13:58,037 --> 00:13:59,958
Are you crazy, He Yuqiong?

235
00:14:00,118 --> 00:14:01,958
I was kidding,
and you actually believed it.

236
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:10,637
They look really good.

237
00:14:14,072 --> 00:14:15,757
Xiaoming is here.

238
00:14:15,998 --> 00:14:16,718
Hello, Madam.

239
00:14:17,078 --> 00:14:18,078
Have you two eaten?

240
00:14:18,198 --> 00:14:18,958
- Not yet.
- Not yet.

241
00:14:19,238 --> 00:14:21,238
A new dumpling store opened
at the intersection.

242
00:14:21,598 --> 00:14:23,238
Tiantian,
take Xiaoming to eat dumplings.

243
00:14:24,437 --> 00:14:26,238
Alright, I earned nearly 300 today.

244
00:14:26,838 --> 00:14:27,557
Let's go there.

245
00:14:27,958 --> 00:14:29,277
Good for you.

246
00:14:32,637 --> 00:14:33,557
Let's go eat dumplings.

247
00:14:34,078 --> 00:14:34,808
Go on.

248
00:14:37,037 --> 00:14:39,037
Hey, why did you throw away my shoes?

249
00:14:39,238 --> 00:14:41,078
You have new ones now.
Why keep the old ones?

250
00:14:42,078 --> 00:14:42,718
Let's go.

251
00:14:42,826 --> 00:14:48,376
(Tiantian Apparel. Welcome)

252
00:14:48,701 --> 00:14:52,397
(Bus No. 53)

253
00:14:52,397 --> 00:14:53,277
21:40.

254
00:14:55,037 --> 00:14:55,958
The bus hasn't come.

255
00:14:59,917 --> 00:15:00,677
What time is it?

256
00:15:06,557 --> 00:15:08,397
21:48.

257
00:15:09,757 --> 00:15:10,397
It's fine.

258
00:15:10,397 --> 00:15:12,397
- Just wait a bit longer.
- What?

259
00:15:12,998 --> 00:15:14,157
Didn't you see what it says?

260
00:15:14,238 --> 00:15:15,437
Last bus at 21:40.

261
00:15:15,437 --> 00:15:16,280
What time is it now?

262
00:15:16,437 --> 00:15:17,757
21:48.

263
00:15:18,157 --> 00:15:19,318
Unless your watch is broken.

264
00:15:20,838 --> 00:15:22,517
This is my mom's watch. It was broken.

265
00:15:22,677 --> 00:15:24,838
I just fixed it today. It's accurate.

266
00:15:29,718 --> 00:15:32,198
It's your fault. I said
we'd eat some dumplings and leave.

267
00:15:32,318 --> 00:15:34,198
But you dragged me around.

268
00:15:34,198 --> 00:15:35,037
What do we do now?

269
00:15:35,517 --> 00:15:38,598
Come on, your mouth was watering
when you looked at those skewers.

270
00:15:38,958 --> 00:15:40,917
I kindly satisfied you,
and now you blame me?

271
00:15:41,517 --> 00:15:42,478
Where are you going?

272
00:15:43,078 --> 00:15:43,797
I'm walking back.

273
00:15:44,478 --> 00:15:45,397
To La City?

274
00:15:45,557 --> 00:15:47,437
I need to get back
to school before dawn.

275
00:15:50,838 --> 00:15:51,917
By walking?

276
00:15:53,437 --> 00:15:54,437
What did you think?

277
00:15:56,677 --> 00:15:57,958
Let me get you a taxi.

278
00:16:01,198 --> 00:16:03,397
Are you showing off you have money?

279
00:16:09,318 --> 00:16:10,958
It hurts so much.

280
00:16:11,557 --> 00:16:13,878
It's all your fault
for throwing away my old shoes.

281
00:16:14,078 --> 00:16:15,677
The new shoes hurt my feet.

282
00:16:16,157 --> 00:16:17,757
New shoes always rub.

283
00:16:18,397 --> 00:16:20,397
I suggested getting a taxi,
but you objected.

284
00:16:20,397 --> 00:16:22,037
There are none now. I can't get you one.

285
00:16:22,557 --> 00:16:24,318
I just didn't want you to waste money.

286
00:16:24,677 --> 00:16:26,677
That's not your money, but your mom's.

287
00:16:27,517 --> 00:16:28,757
Be nice.

288
00:16:31,544 --> 00:16:33,478
It hurts so much.

289
00:16:35,078 --> 00:16:36,557
I can't walk anymore.

290
00:16:44,157 --> 00:16:45,198
Miss Ren, please get on.

291
00:16:48,397 --> 00:16:50,397
I have legs. I can walk myself.

292
00:16:50,797 --> 00:16:52,277
Why are you so stubborn?

293
00:16:53,878 --> 00:16:55,037
You stubborn donkey.

294
00:16:56,917 --> 00:16:58,397
I'll beat you up.

295
00:17:01,238 --> 00:17:02,958
Start running, and it won't hurt.

296
00:17:04,197 --> 00:17:05,677
I can't run.

297
00:17:06,518 --> 00:17:07,397
Run faster!

298
00:17:07,917 --> 00:17:09,118
How can I run faster?

299
00:17:11,197 --> 00:17:12,237
Wait up, He Yuqiong.

300
00:17:14,197 --> 00:17:15,677
You're way too slow.

301
00:17:15,677 --> 00:17:16,558
I can't do it.

302
00:17:16,758 --> 00:17:19,318
Why should we cross this bridge?
We could have taken a good path.

303
00:17:19,558 --> 00:17:21,237
Wait up, He Yuqiong.

304
00:17:24,078 --> 00:17:26,717
I can't go on. I can't walk anymore.

305
00:17:31,758 --> 00:17:32,758
Does it hurt that much?

306
00:17:38,518 --> 00:17:39,157
So much blood.

307
00:17:39,878 --> 00:17:40,997
Your foot is injured.

308
00:17:49,598 --> 00:17:50,424
Water.

309
00:18:02,157 --> 00:18:03,397
You've drunk it.

310
00:18:04,118 --> 00:18:04,758
Drink it all.

311
00:18:15,997 --> 00:18:17,477
Which college do you want to enter?

312
00:18:18,957 --> 00:18:20,598
The exam is over a year away. No rush.

313
00:18:21,997 --> 00:18:25,397
Do you think a year is long? Time flies.

314
00:18:27,838 --> 00:18:30,078
That's exactly
what my homeroom teacher says.

315
00:18:32,637 --> 00:18:35,197
Don't you look up college info early

316
00:18:35,518 --> 00:18:37,798
and check college admission scores?

317
00:18:38,078 --> 00:18:40,118
Do you know
about a top or key university?

318
00:18:40,437 --> 00:18:42,038
No, but I know what 110 means.

319
00:18:42,118 --> 00:18:43,078
Emergency call number.

320
00:18:44,437 --> 00:18:46,397
The exam weeds out people like you.

321
00:18:47,917 --> 00:18:49,798
No need to weed me out.
I'm not taking it.

322
00:18:52,717 --> 00:18:53,237
What?

323
00:18:56,558 --> 00:18:58,157
After high school, I'll learn a trade.

324
00:18:58,237 --> 00:18:59,917
I'll work early to ease my mom's burden.

325
00:19:03,397 --> 00:19:04,677
You're short-sighted.

326
00:19:04,758 --> 00:19:06,477
You'll let your mom down.

327
00:19:08,477 --> 00:19:09,976
I just hate sitting in the classroom.

328
00:19:09,976 --> 00:19:11,758
It's super boring.
I don't want to study.

329
00:19:13,917 --> 00:19:17,318
He Yuqiong,
if you give up, I'll give up too.

330
00:19:17,397 --> 00:19:18,157
What?

331
00:19:19,038 --> 00:19:21,397
No way. You have to go to college.

332
00:19:25,157 --> 00:19:26,477
You must go. How can you not?

333
00:19:27,437 --> 00:19:28,318
Will you?

334
00:19:29,997 --> 00:19:30,558
Yes.

335
00:19:30,838 --> 00:19:31,832
Will you take the exam?

336
00:19:32,518 --> 00:19:33,078
Yes.

337
00:19:33,997 --> 00:19:35,437
I'll definitely take it.

338
00:19:36,437 --> 00:19:38,437
You have to work hard. Got it?

339
00:19:38,637 --> 00:19:39,558
Okay, I'll try.

340
00:19:56,078 --> 00:19:57,717
Which university
do you want to get into?

341
00:20:02,598 --> 00:20:03,558
Bai Shu wants

342
00:20:05,437 --> 00:20:06,798
to get into Qingzhou University.

343
00:20:08,558 --> 00:20:10,917
Qingzhou University?
Isn't that every parent's choice?

344
00:20:11,038 --> 00:20:12,758
When adults praise kids for being smart,

345
00:20:12,758 --> 00:20:15,197
they say the kids will get
into Qingzhou University.

346
00:20:20,397 --> 00:20:22,558
You'll get into Qingzhou University too.

347
00:20:27,518 --> 00:20:28,078
Me?

348
00:20:29,637 --> 00:20:30,717
I can't get in.

349
00:20:31,677 --> 00:20:32,598
No, you can't think so.

350
00:20:33,038 --> 00:20:35,078
You haven't even tried.
How do you know you'll fail?

351
00:20:37,677 --> 00:20:40,598
In our class, only Bai Shu could get in.

352
00:20:41,558 --> 00:20:43,237
I don't think you're worse than Bai Shu.

353
00:20:44,637 --> 00:20:45,838
Look, in your class,

354
00:20:46,078 --> 00:20:48,878
you went from average
to top rank in one semester.

355
00:20:48,878 --> 00:20:49,518
That's amazing.

356
00:20:49,838 --> 00:20:51,078
Why underestimate yourself?

357
00:20:52,957 --> 00:20:56,157
She's like a bird,
while I'm a mosquito in the ditch.

358
00:20:56,838 --> 00:20:58,598
Can I expect to fly high?

359
00:21:03,758 --> 00:21:05,078
Can you walk back to school?

360
00:21:06,437 --> 00:21:07,558
I can't walk anymore.

361
00:21:09,318 --> 00:21:09,917
Get up.

362
00:21:13,997 --> 00:21:14,677
Stand up.

363
00:21:15,717 --> 00:21:16,997
Just leave me alone.

364
00:21:18,397 --> 00:21:19,917
It hurts so much.

365
00:21:24,237 --> 00:21:25,717
He Yuqiong, where are you going?

366
00:21:27,278 --> 00:21:28,677
Don't leave me here!

367
00:21:30,758 --> 00:21:34,917
If you can walk to me,
you can move up 20 spots in the grade.

368
00:21:41,038 --> 00:21:42,237
It's not funny.

369
00:21:43,758 --> 00:21:46,437
If you don't,
you're admitting you're a loser.

370
00:21:49,518 --> 00:21:50,838
You're the loser.

371
00:22:13,278 --> 00:22:14,917
Come on, try harder.

372
00:22:18,157 --> 00:22:19,637
I can't run.

373
00:22:19,798 --> 00:22:22,318
Walk to me, and you'll move up 50 spots.

374
00:22:22,997 --> 00:22:24,798
Are you walking a dog?

375
00:22:25,078 --> 00:22:26,360
Walk here,

376
00:22:26,360 --> 00:22:29,397
and you'll get
into a top or key university.

377
00:22:30,038 --> 00:22:32,677
Come on, do you even know what they are?

378
00:22:33,397 --> 00:22:34,798
Whether I know isn't important.

379
00:22:35,078 --> 00:22:36,677
You getting in is what matters.

380
00:22:39,798 --> 00:22:41,558
Ren Xiaoming, you're the best!

381
00:22:42,997 --> 00:22:46,838
Do you wish to go to Qingzhou University
and leave Qidaohezi?

382
00:22:47,798 --> 00:22:48,838
Yes.

383
00:22:51,917 --> 00:22:52,798
Wait for me.

384
00:22:53,477 --> 00:22:54,157
Hurry up.

385
00:23:01,838 --> 00:23:05,477
Very soon, you'll be sleeping
in your cozy dorm.

386
00:23:09,078 --> 00:23:11,078
Maybe loosen your shoelaces a bit more?

387
00:23:12,157 --> 00:23:13,118
- You...
- Wait.

388
00:23:13,518 --> 00:23:14,157
Be careful.

389
00:23:14,397 --> 00:23:15,677
It's fine. Just a moment.

390
00:23:15,677 --> 00:23:17,397
What's wrong? Are you okay?

391
00:23:18,917 --> 00:23:19,717
My legs gave out.

392
00:23:20,078 --> 00:23:20,888
Hold on.

393
00:23:21,838 --> 00:23:22,477
Loosen them.

394
00:23:23,397 --> 00:23:24,318
Loosen the shoelaces.

395
00:23:24,318 --> 00:23:25,997
Okay, enough.

396
00:23:26,717 --> 00:23:27,518
You liar.

397
00:23:28,558 --> 00:23:31,197
I've walked all night.
I almost can't walk.

398
00:23:31,838 --> 00:23:33,558
Hey, I walked all night with you too.

399
00:23:33,957 --> 00:23:36,558
I envy you having a good friend like me.

400
00:23:37,558 --> 00:23:38,758
Have you been moved?

401
00:23:40,637 --> 00:23:42,477
- Let me help you.
- No.

402
00:23:43,237 --> 00:23:44,677
Let me help you. Why so stubborn?

403
00:23:46,157 --> 00:23:47,078
Be nice.

404
00:23:50,437 --> 00:23:51,318
Almost there.

405
00:23:52,197 --> 00:23:53,112
Just 20 meters to go.

406
00:23:53,558 --> 00:23:55,518
Come on. Almost there.

407
00:23:56,477 --> 00:23:58,397
20 meters to go. 19 meters to go.

408
00:24:01,758 --> 00:24:03,397
- What's that?
- Hold on.

409
00:24:04,397 --> 00:24:06,078
Who's there? So many people.

410
00:24:06,278 --> 00:24:07,118
Is that her?

411
00:24:07,798 --> 00:24:08,397
Your mom.

412
00:24:11,318 --> 00:24:12,197
Ren Xiaoming.

413
00:24:15,038 --> 00:24:15,736
Careful!

414
00:24:16,318 --> 00:24:18,157
My leg's broken.

415
00:24:18,437 --> 00:24:20,118
- Slow down.
- It hurts.

416
00:24:20,118 --> 00:24:21,917
Ren Xiaoming! What are you doing?

417
00:24:23,518 --> 00:24:24,440
Come out!

418
00:24:25,477 --> 00:24:26,318
She can't get up.

419
00:24:26,518 --> 00:24:28,518
He Yuqiong! What did you do to her?

420
00:24:29,397 --> 00:24:30,397
She broke her leg.

421
00:24:41,558 --> 00:24:42,677
What happened to your leg?

422
00:24:43,237 --> 00:24:44,440
None of your business.

423
00:24:50,118 --> 00:24:51,798
Your teacher called me last night.

424
00:24:51,957 --> 00:24:53,157
You've got some nerve.

425
00:24:53,677 --> 00:24:54,637
What are you doing?

426
00:24:55,558 --> 00:24:57,957
You're really getting good
at embarrassing me.

427
00:24:58,397 --> 00:24:59,957
Her leg is broken. Stop hitting her.

428
00:24:59,957 --> 00:25:01,558
- That's why I'm able to hit her.
- Mom!

429
00:25:02,518 --> 00:25:03,637
- Mom!
- You can't run away.

430
00:25:06,038 --> 00:25:06,957
Try to run again.

431
00:25:10,598 --> 00:25:12,518
Xiaoming, you rest on my bed.

432
00:25:13,118 --> 00:25:14,677
That's your bed, not mine.

433
00:25:14,917 --> 00:25:15,878
Stop playing the victim.

434
00:25:16,437 --> 00:25:18,397
The sofa is your bed.
Go lie down on the sofa.

435
00:25:21,437 --> 00:25:24,118
Xiaoming, rest on the sofa for a while.

436
00:25:32,397 --> 00:25:33,078
You're home.

437
00:25:35,237 --> 00:25:35,878
What happened?

438
00:25:37,518 --> 00:25:39,477
She fell into a drainage ditch
by accident.

439
00:25:40,917 --> 00:25:41,677
What's wrong?

440
00:25:49,637 --> 00:25:52,197
Stop it. Everyone's asking me for money.

441
00:25:52,237 --> 00:25:53,598
But who else should I ask?

442
00:25:54,397 --> 00:25:55,917
- Xiaoming's sponsorship fee.
- Sponsorship fee?

443
00:25:56,437 --> 00:25:58,038
I don't even dare go back to the office.

444
00:25:58,038 --> 00:25:59,318
People wait outside the company.

445
00:25:59,598 --> 00:26:00,677
How is it such a deficit?

446
00:26:01,038 --> 00:26:02,518
The suppliers won't settle accounts.

447
00:26:02,598 --> 00:26:03,637
So I can't pay them.

448
00:26:04,038 --> 00:26:05,598
What happened?

449
00:26:05,917 --> 00:26:09,078
Big trouble. Life-threatening trouble.

450
00:26:09,677 --> 00:26:10,518
Driving me to death?

451
00:26:10,677 --> 00:26:12,758
Fine. Then let's die together.

452
00:26:13,518 --> 00:26:15,237
What am I supposed to do?

453
00:26:22,318 --> 00:26:23,160
Mom.

454
00:26:24,477 --> 00:26:25,637
Why is Mr. Sun crying?

455
00:26:27,677 --> 00:26:28,760
Business isn't going well.

456
00:26:29,838 --> 00:26:31,758
So he takes it out on you?

457
00:26:33,917 --> 00:26:35,717
You seemed tough
when you were hitting me.

458
00:26:35,798 --> 00:26:37,157
Why so quiet now?

459
00:26:38,637 --> 00:26:39,518
I'm tired.

460
00:26:40,038 --> 00:26:41,758
Adults have struggles too.

461
00:26:42,477 --> 00:26:43,576
You only think of yourself.

462
00:26:43,758 --> 00:26:45,518
Why don't you think
about how you grew up?

463
00:26:46,397 --> 00:26:47,278
You look down on me.

464
00:26:47,758 --> 00:26:49,637
If you think I live like a loser,

465
00:26:49,917 --> 00:26:50,917
don't learn from me.

466
00:26:51,437 --> 00:26:52,518
Stay away from He Yuqiong.

467
00:26:52,598 --> 00:26:53,477
If you don't,

468
00:26:53,477 --> 00:26:54,917
your fate will be worse than mine.

469
00:26:55,518 --> 00:26:57,278
There's nothing between him and me.

470
00:26:57,278 --> 00:26:58,437
You got the wrong idea.

471
00:26:58,598 --> 00:26:59,558
Am I blind?

472
00:27:03,598 --> 00:27:06,197
Don't worry. I won't end up like you.

473
00:27:06,878 --> 00:27:08,038
I won't let you laugh at me.

474
00:27:17,038 --> 00:27:18,078
Keep your word.

475
00:27:35,224 --> 00:27:38,648
(One month later)

476
00:27:43,477 --> 00:27:44,184
Here you are.

477
00:27:47,278 --> 00:27:49,318
Xiaoming, your leg is better.

478
00:27:49,558 --> 00:27:50,936
Why do I still wash fruit for you?

479
00:27:52,118 --> 00:27:53,518
I've cooked for you for many years.

480
00:27:53,518 --> 00:27:55,558
And you're complaining
about washing fruit?

481
00:27:56,118 --> 00:27:57,437
I can take care of you.

482
00:27:57,758 --> 00:28:01,038
But the doc says once the cast is off,
you need to walk around more.

483
00:28:01,717 --> 00:28:03,197
Otherwise, your muscles will atrophy.

484
00:28:03,957 --> 00:28:06,078
Alright, got it. You may leave.

485
00:28:12,477 --> 00:28:13,592
Why are you standing here?

486
00:28:14,637 --> 00:28:16,598
I'm studying. No time to chat with you.

487
00:28:20,758 --> 00:28:21,598
What do you want?

488
00:28:28,477 --> 00:28:30,477
Go back to your room.
Can't you understand me?

489
00:28:30,798 --> 00:28:31,917
Go back to your room!

490
00:28:39,558 --> 00:28:41,318
- Xiaofei.
- Bai Shu.

491
00:28:44,278 --> 00:28:45,078
Bai Shu!

492
00:28:45,878 --> 00:28:47,878
- How come you're here?
- I missed you.

493
00:28:49,798 --> 00:28:50,717
How's your leg?

494
00:28:53,598 --> 00:28:54,518
I got the cast off.

495
00:28:56,838 --> 00:28:58,318
You didn't even take the final exams.

496
00:28:58,717 --> 00:29:00,078
I haven't seen you in two months.

497
00:29:00,318 --> 00:29:01,397
I did it on purpose.

498
00:29:01,798 --> 00:29:03,256
Haven't been to school for so long.

499
00:29:03,397 --> 00:29:04,758
I couldn't do well on the exam.

500
00:29:04,758 --> 00:29:05,558
So I skipped it.

501
00:29:07,197 --> 00:29:09,997
I know you've missed classes.
I'm here to tutor you.

502
00:29:10,518 --> 00:29:11,997
Does your mom know you're here?

503
00:29:12,717 --> 00:29:15,477
She's been busy lately, always out
during the day. She won't notice.

504
00:29:22,477 --> 00:29:24,637
Go back. We need to study, okay?

505
00:29:26,518 --> 00:29:27,717
Go back to your room.

506
00:29:29,637 --> 00:29:32,056
You promised to take me
on the Ferris wheel for my birthday.

507
00:29:32,518 --> 00:29:33,397
You big liar!

508
00:29:35,917 --> 00:29:37,318
- Today's your birthday?
- Today's your birthday?

509
00:29:39,437 --> 00:29:42,118
What are we waiting for? Let's go.

510
00:29:43,078 --> 00:29:43,928
Come on.

511
00:29:47,118 --> 00:29:48,798
Doesn't your mom care about Xiaofei?

512
00:29:49,118 --> 00:29:50,616
How could she forget his birthday?

513
00:29:52,278 --> 00:29:55,197
She didn't forget.
She just never celebrates it.

514
00:29:56,318 --> 00:29:57,197
Why not?

515
00:29:58,598 --> 00:29:59,197
I don't know.

516
00:30:00,838 --> 00:30:03,838
I remember that before Xiaofei was born,

517
00:30:04,477 --> 00:30:05,917
my mom celebrated my birthday once.

518
00:30:06,397 --> 00:30:07,437
I had cake once.

519
00:30:09,118 --> 00:30:10,838
But she never
celebrated Xiaofei's birthday.

520
00:30:12,157 --> 00:30:12,917
Forget it.

521
00:30:14,318 --> 00:30:15,798
Any gossip about me at school?

522
00:30:15,838 --> 00:30:16,957
Of course.

523
00:30:17,157 --> 00:30:19,917
They say you eloped
with a hot guy and got caught.

524
00:30:19,997 --> 00:30:21,437
You jumped off a bridge for love,

525
00:30:21,437 --> 00:30:23,558
but the river was dry
and you both broke your legs.

526
00:30:25,758 --> 00:30:26,997
What?

527
00:30:26,997 --> 00:30:27,917
- What's wrong?
- It's true.

528
00:30:28,237 --> 00:30:29,197
Get lost.

529
00:30:29,637 --> 00:30:30,798
Xiaoming, are you okay?

530
00:30:31,318 --> 00:30:32,838
I might hit you on your birthday.

531
00:30:32,838 --> 00:30:34,168
Come with me, Xiaofei.

532
00:30:34,168 --> 00:30:35,997
- Go with me.
- Okay.

533
00:30:36,038 --> 00:30:37,997
Die for love? Jump off a bridge?

534
00:30:37,997 --> 00:30:39,677
We both broke your legs? Ugh!

535
00:30:49,957 --> 00:30:52,878
What should I do?
I might as well jump from here.

536
00:30:54,917 --> 00:30:56,598
Sing Xiaofei the birthday song first.

537
00:30:58,278 --> 00:31:01,717
♪Happy birthday to you♪

538
00:31:02,477 --> 00:31:05,917
♪Happy birthday to you♪

539
00:31:06,677 --> 00:31:10,677
♪Happy birthday to you♪

540
00:31:11,237 --> 00:31:14,878
♪Happy birthday to you♪

541
00:31:15,717 --> 00:31:17,038
Happy birthday, Xiaofei.

542
00:31:17,118 --> 00:31:18,477
Happy birthday, Xiaofei.

543
00:31:18,598 --> 00:31:20,397
I'll give the biggest bubble
to both of you.

544
00:31:23,278 --> 00:31:24,318
It is pretty big.

545
00:31:29,558 --> 00:31:32,118
Xiaofei, we're almost at the top.
Make a wish.

546
00:31:34,397 --> 00:31:37,798
I hope I can spend every birthday
with both of you,

547
00:31:38,038 --> 00:31:39,798
coming to ride the Ferris wheel.

548
00:31:40,237 --> 00:31:42,437
But don't leave Xiaoming in Qidaohezi

549
00:31:42,878 --> 00:31:44,477
just to celebrate my birthday.

550
00:31:45,118 --> 00:31:47,038
I hope she will get better and better,

551
00:31:47,477 --> 00:31:50,278
get into her dream university,
and go wherever she wants.

552
00:31:59,197 --> 00:32:01,518
Why involve me in your birthday wish?

553
00:32:01,878 --> 00:32:05,477
Xiaofei, don't worry.
No matter where Xiaoming is,

554
00:32:05,997 --> 00:32:07,320
she won't forget your birthday.

555
00:32:07,798 --> 00:32:09,016
She'll celebrate it with you.

556
00:32:09,237 --> 00:32:10,072
Okay.

557
00:32:11,758 --> 00:32:13,878
That's what you said. I didn't say that.

558
00:32:15,558 --> 00:32:17,118
Bai Shu, what about you?

559
00:32:18,078 --> 00:32:19,878
Will you come back to Qidaohezi?

560
00:32:26,437 --> 00:32:29,157
The world looks quite interesting
from the Ferris wheel.

561
00:32:35,805 --> 00:32:38,237
(Qidaohezi, 2023)

562
00:32:38,237 --> 00:32:40,917
I promised to come back
to celebrate your birthday with you.

563
00:32:43,717 --> 00:32:47,118
I'm sorry. I broke my promise.

564
00:32:49,598 --> 00:32:54,598
Then will you come back
for my birthday this year?

565
00:32:59,997 --> 00:33:00,997
What about the New Year?

566
00:33:02,637 --> 00:33:03,917
Will you come back too?

567
00:33:13,397 --> 00:33:14,558
What about Bai Shu?

568
00:33:15,798 --> 00:33:16,917
Will she come back too?

569
00:33:26,518 --> 00:33:30,957
(The same event is remembered
differently by everyone.)

570
00:33:31,758 --> 00:33:34,197
(Xiaofei remembers
how happy he was on his birthday.)

571
00:33:34,758 --> 00:33:35,957
(But I only remember)

572
00:33:36,717 --> 00:33:39,838
(that everything started getting worse
from that day on.)

573
00:33:41,157 --> 00:33:43,118
Xiaoming, I'm really happy today.

574
00:33:43,917 --> 00:33:45,038
(La City, 2006)
You sure had fun.

575
00:33:45,717 --> 00:33:46,997
Don't sell me out.

576
00:33:47,717 --> 00:33:49,038
Later, you insist

577
00:33:49,717 --> 00:33:51,798
that it was your idea to go out. Got it?

578
00:33:51,878 --> 00:33:53,838
Don't worry. I won't spill the secret.

579
00:34:09,397 --> 00:34:10,597
Why isn't Mom home?

580
00:34:10,997 --> 00:34:12,037
Isn't that perfect?

581
00:34:12,397 --> 00:34:13,198
She won't catch us.

582
00:34:15,397 --> 00:34:15,997
Help me.

583
00:34:25,437 --> 00:34:25,957
Mom.

584
00:34:29,397 --> 00:34:30,456
What are you doing here?

585
00:34:31,957 --> 00:34:32,997
It's my fault.

586
00:34:33,678 --> 00:34:35,798
I asked Xiaoming to take me out.

587
00:34:47,238 --> 00:34:48,437
Sun Jinfu...

588
00:34:51,278 --> 00:34:52,397
He ran away.

589
00:34:57,517 --> 00:34:59,318
He hasn't given me

590
00:35:01,758 --> 00:35:03,477
your sponsorship fee.

591
00:35:14,957 --> 00:35:18,718
(Sun Jinfu ran off with over six million
from his business partners?)

592
00:35:20,597 --> 00:35:21,557
(Pay us)
Pay us back.

593
00:35:21,838 --> 00:35:22,840
There's someone inside.

594
00:35:23,397 --> 00:35:24,158
Repay the money.

595
00:35:24,198 --> 00:35:26,838
You owe us millions.
Are you trying to drive us to death?

596
00:35:27,278 --> 00:35:28,077
Repay the money!

597
00:35:28,117 --> 00:35:28,638
Come out!

598
00:35:28,878 --> 00:35:29,397
Come out!

599
00:35:29,638 --> 00:35:30,397
Repay the money!

600
00:35:30,397 --> 00:35:31,278
You sell your house.

601
00:35:32,238 --> 00:35:33,397
Repay the money!

602
00:35:33,397 --> 00:35:34,597
- Come out!
- Repay the money!

603
00:35:34,838 --> 00:35:35,437
Come out!

604
00:36:15,597 --> 00:36:16,597
Xiaoming.

605
00:36:19,238 --> 00:36:20,198
What are you doing here?

606
00:36:21,238 --> 00:36:22,037
Your dad ran away.

607
00:36:22,358 --> 00:36:23,997
My mom ran away too.

608
00:36:26,318 --> 00:36:28,117
Your dad and mom ran away together?

609
00:36:30,517 --> 00:36:33,477
They ran away separately.

610
00:36:40,517 --> 00:36:42,238
Your parents are divorced.

611
00:36:42,917 --> 00:36:46,278
Your dad is in trouble.
Why did your mom run?

612
00:36:47,318 --> 00:36:50,358
My mom wanted to make money.
So she invested.

613
00:36:50,917 --> 00:36:52,758
She borrowed a lot of money from others.

614
00:36:53,397 --> 00:36:55,557
She's been gone for days.

615
00:36:59,437 --> 00:37:01,198
She just left you alone at home?

616
00:37:01,718 --> 00:37:05,238
She left Xiaoxue and me with my stepdad.

617
00:37:13,117 --> 00:37:14,597
Can I go to your place?

618
00:37:17,758 --> 00:37:19,517
Don't you hate us?

619
00:37:19,718 --> 00:37:23,077
Compared to you, I hate my stepdad more.

620
00:37:23,557 --> 00:37:26,557
Alright, you're pretty honest.

621
00:37:27,198 --> 00:37:29,557
He has long wanted
to abandon my mom and me.

622
00:37:29,718 --> 00:37:33,198
After my mom left,
he didn't even make me food.

623
00:37:39,037 --> 00:37:40,117
How long have you been out?

624
00:37:41,077 --> 00:37:41,917
Two days.

625
00:37:44,597 --> 00:37:46,198
Where have you been these two days?

626
00:37:46,798 --> 00:37:47,638
Malls.

627
00:37:48,437 --> 00:37:51,718
During the day,
Xiaoxue and I just wander around malls.

628
00:37:52,597 --> 00:37:56,798
At night,
Xiaoxue and I sleep in stairwells.

629
00:37:57,477 --> 00:37:58,397
What do you eat?

630
00:38:01,077 --> 00:38:01,597
This.

631
00:38:03,397 --> 00:38:04,758
Just this?

632
00:38:06,238 --> 00:38:10,517
I only licked it for a bit.
Then I packed it up.

633
00:38:10,997 --> 00:38:12,318
You can't eat this.

634
00:38:14,037 --> 00:38:15,597
I don't want it.

635
00:38:22,678 --> 00:38:24,798
Come on.
Let me get you something to eat.

636
00:38:26,758 --> 00:38:27,437
What's wrong?

637
00:38:28,517 --> 00:38:31,032
I haven't eaten. My legs feel weak.

638
00:38:31,032 --> 00:38:33,816
I feel a bit dizzy and can't walk.

639
00:38:35,037 --> 00:38:36,997
Then what? Not going?

640
00:38:37,397 --> 00:38:38,318
Carry me.

641
00:38:39,758 --> 00:38:40,504
What?

642
00:38:47,597 --> 00:38:48,798
You win.

643
00:38:52,838 --> 00:38:53,437
Step up.

644
00:38:57,917 --> 00:38:58,840
Get on.

645
00:39:01,678 --> 00:39:02,957
I haven't even carried Xiaofei.

646
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:13,444
(Qidaohezi, 2023)

647
00:39:19,117 --> 00:39:20,077
Let me help you.

648
00:39:20,077 --> 00:39:20,758
No, thanks.

649
00:39:22,158 --> 00:39:24,397
Is the Women's Federation upstairs?

650
00:39:24,758 --> 00:39:26,198
Sure. What's up?

651
00:39:26,758 --> 00:39:29,437
If a woman is abused at home,
will the Women's Federation step in?

652
00:39:30,077 --> 00:39:32,437
We handle anything related
to women and children.

653
00:39:32,718 --> 00:39:35,517
What if it didn't happen in Qidaohezi?
Do you still handle it?

654
00:39:35,917 --> 00:39:36,917
Then you...

655
00:39:39,517 --> 00:39:42,358
Xiaoming, what are you doing here?

656
00:39:43,238 --> 00:39:43,997
Yuanyuan?

657
00:39:44,517 --> 00:39:45,678
Little Monkey!

658
00:39:46,638 --> 00:39:48,997
It's been years.
Why do you still call me that?

659
00:39:48,997 --> 00:39:51,077
Your dad is Monkey King.
So you are Little Monkey.

660
00:39:52,037 --> 00:39:53,917
So good to see you again.

661
00:39:54,037 --> 00:39:55,678
I haven't seen you in years.

662
00:39:56,420 --> 00:39:58,917
(In 2006, La City)

663
00:39:58,917 --> 00:40:02,158
Yuanyuan, is it tasty?

664
00:40:02,437 --> 00:40:03,384
Yes.

665
00:40:06,557 --> 00:40:08,957
Don't you avoid fried food?

666
00:40:09,437 --> 00:40:10,758
The drumsticks are fried.

667
00:40:12,638 --> 00:40:13,638
Don't listen to her.

668
00:40:13,997 --> 00:40:15,957
Ren Xiaoming, where are your manners?

669
00:40:16,397 --> 00:40:17,358
Use serving chopsticks.

670
00:40:24,397 --> 00:40:26,424
Yuanyuan.

671
00:40:29,158 --> 00:40:31,077
I'm not returning tit for tat.

672
00:40:31,718 --> 00:40:32,997
Your dad loves you the most.

673
00:40:33,437 --> 00:40:36,117
He's already made a mistake.
You're still young.

674
00:40:36,678 --> 00:40:40,638
Remember, don't attack
people's sore spots with words.

675
00:40:40,917 --> 00:40:42,318
Don't speak harshly.

676
00:40:44,477 --> 00:40:46,917
No matter how angry you are,
don't say harsh words.

677
00:40:47,238 --> 00:40:48,397
Three of you, remember this.

678
00:40:48,917 --> 00:40:50,638
Alright, stop crying.

679
00:40:51,278 --> 00:40:53,278
Otherwise, the creditors
will hear you crying.

680
00:40:53,517 --> 00:40:56,798
Stop crying. Eat your food.

681
00:40:57,318 --> 00:40:58,758
You made her cry.

682
00:40:58,798 --> 00:40:59,318
Shut up.

683
00:40:59,997 --> 00:41:00,638
Try this.

684
00:41:02,997 --> 00:41:03,957
Come on.

685
00:41:05,838 --> 00:41:06,397
Go on.

686
00:41:07,678 --> 00:41:10,517
Ms. Ren, I'm sorry. I was wrong.

687
00:41:11,238 --> 00:41:13,997
I was jealous of you being with Dad.

688
00:41:14,917 --> 00:41:17,678
Dad is the best person to me.

689
00:41:24,997 --> 00:41:25,838
This is for you.

690
00:41:27,077 --> 00:41:28,278
Thanks, Xiaofei.

691
00:41:29,557 --> 00:41:31,557
Sounds so sweet.

692
00:41:33,358 --> 00:41:37,517
Ms. Ren, can I live with you?

693
00:41:42,638 --> 00:41:45,597
What if your mom comes back for you?

694
00:41:45,957 --> 00:41:48,158
If my mom comes back for me,

695
00:41:48,397 --> 00:41:50,997
I definitely won't stay with you.

696
00:41:51,437 --> 00:41:53,517
I'll go back and live with my mom.

697
00:41:54,117 --> 00:41:56,597
You really are an honest kid.

698
00:41:57,318 --> 00:41:58,318
You eat.

699
00:42:00,957 --> 00:42:02,477
Wipe away your tears.

700
00:42:08,638 --> 00:42:10,077
Put this hand here.

701
00:42:10,278 --> 00:42:11,917
Put it here. Hold the bowl.

702
00:42:18,718 --> 00:42:19,957
How are Ms. Ren and Xiaofei?

703
00:42:20,917 --> 00:42:21,798
They're good.

704
00:42:23,037 --> 00:42:25,238
My mom just got married last month.

705
00:42:25,477 --> 00:42:26,477
They're newlyweds.

706
00:42:32,798 --> 00:42:34,037
Sorry, I forgot about your dad.

707
00:42:35,278 --> 00:42:38,117
It's okay. My dad told me about that.

708
00:42:39,517 --> 00:42:42,678
In the second year of his sentence,
my dad asked Ms. Ren for a divorce.

709
00:42:42,838 --> 00:42:44,077
Ms. Ren objected back then.

710
00:42:44,198 --> 00:42:45,318
But my dad insisted on it.

711
00:42:47,238 --> 00:42:47,917
Thanks.

712
00:42:51,077 --> 00:42:52,838
Actually, Mr. Sun is a good man.

713
00:42:53,557 --> 00:42:55,437
He was just afraid of implicating us.

714
00:42:56,285 --> 00:42:58,397
(La City, 2006)

715
00:42:58,397 --> 00:43:01,278
Ms. Ren Meiyan,
Sun Jinfu has been caught.

716
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
